Meanwhile, Nolan progresses in the uncovering the affairs of Grosvenor and Crombie; according to his old friend Joshua, undoubtedly the Stryx are responsible.

Almost 4 years after an extra-terrestrial attack that wiped out most of the armed forces and that made the governments of the different countries worldwide kneel, the Earth is nothing but a wide playground for its new masters, former Mafiosi, criminals and other religious fanatics. These latter, having now become genuine war lords, call on the services of a mercenary and weaponry corporation, having survived to the invasion and capable of providing men, weapons and ammunition, or even essential products: Blackfire Industries.

It is in this environment of chaos and war that we discover the Chaos Team, a mercenary unit linked to Blackfire and led by John Clem, on a protection mission in Granada, for the new Pope.
name: Feedback

description: Joined by Catwoman and Huntress, Batwoman takes on Edel Nacht and his Tenebrae army. Back at the cabaret, Zatanna pays a price for her attempt to help.

description: Disney• Pixar is on a winning streak, and The Good Dinosaur will be no exception! Tying to the holiday release of The Good Dinosaur, this Cinestory Comic will engage readers with its unique storytelling that follows the adventures of the young dinosaur Arlo by adapting the film script to comic format, and using screen grabs of the film to create a continuous book-length comic story! Much like Joe Books has done with their successful Disney's Frozen and Disney• Pixar's Inside Out Cinestory albums - The Good Dinosaur will be a hit with all fans of animation and comics!
name: GN

description: Free from prison. Trapped in time. Doing Time is an original graphic novel about a colorful cast of convicts running for freedom while the law - and time itself - closes in on them.
name: GN

description: DISOWNED BY THE "PURE" RACES, HALF-ELVES ARE FATED TO DISAPPEAR. WILL THE CHOSEN ONE BE CAPABLE OF CHANGING THE DESTINY OF THE HALF-ELVES? The Half-Elves have no country, no home, no king, no unity, they are hybrid people who live scattered and dispersed. Detested by the "pure" races, they are persecuted, hunted, banished, and imprisoned, if they are not simply eliminated at birth. But times change. Under the leadership of Naah-Taal, the chosen one, the time for the Great Assembly has come...
name: The Chosen Half-Elf 1/2

description:
Dreadwing, Serpentus (now trapped in a female minotaur's body) and Dark Bird are traveling to the powerful secret at Jade-Realm's core via passages through time amber. And woe betide the denizens of any facet-realm they pass through along the way -- like the Gnuoms! These humble, boisterous peanut farmers have lived in peace, enjoying their fermented-peanut ale (or Nut Punch). Now this terrifying trio is about to bulldoze right over them...or will Dreadwing's party suffer the wrath of a Nut Punch attack instead?

Note: The digital edition (2/10/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Atlanta, 1864. Eglantine has discovered what Emperor Napoleon III plans to negotiate with the Confederate States of the South: the use of a monstrous and mystical, living weapon discovered in the ruins of a Mayan temple. Meanwhile, Zelda, Gavroche, and Georges, taken prisoner by the Confederates, are transferred by train towards Atlanta where General Hood wants to question them before initiating the final battle.
name: Atlanta 1/2

description:
"For a Few Credits More"

Hired by the Galactic Shogunate to eliminate the bunny Mortimer, the "greatest threat" to its rule, bounty hunters Blaze and Gruffyd were betrayed, and so adopted Mortimer instead. Now a group of mighty space vikings wants to hire Blaze to get rare medicine for their sick leader, a mission not warlike enough for the vikings to do themselves. But the drug can only be found in the Shogunate's possession, and their forces are ready to fix the bounty hunters that ail them and get back that rabbit!

Note: The digital edition (2/10/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Poli (the titular Interceptor herself) and Weep (badass rebel kid) find themselves at the mercy of Sherriff Arden Reeve and the blood-drunk Baroness of the North, Matilda. Trapped in a vampire prison, surrounded on all sides and dangerously pissed off, Poli and Weep fight for survival as the fates of two worlds hang in the balance! From Donny Cates and Dylan Burnett with a variant cover from Nick "actual vampire" Pitarra (The Manhattan Projects).
A young Buddhist monk must defeat luchador demons and resist the thrall of an enchanted dagger in order to reclaim her own destiny and end a cycle of violence that stretches across lifetimes!
Diana discovers a new mission-perhaps she can save Themyscira by saving the people of Man’s World from the Duke of Deception!

description: CAPTAIN AMERICA and FALCON are off to Lagos to take down a rogue ex-Hydra operative. But are they looking for the right man? Follow BUCKY BARNES, BROCK RUMLOW and STEVE ROGERS as they each cope with the fall-out from the events of CAPTAIN AMERICA: THE WINTER SOLDIER. While Bucky is haunted by the ghosts of his past, he tries to uncover the mystery of his origin. Meanwhile, Rumlow examines his loyalties in the aftermath of the Triskelion explosion. Can anyone be trusted? Find out in this prelude to CAPTAIN AMERICA: CIVIL WAR!

description:
Welcome in the Rif!

Early 20's, Léon and Calixte, the two main characters, try to sale weapons to the rebels in Tanger. They obviously ignore their little traffic will push them to face arrests, torture, rebellion. They figured to become Lords, their journey is far to its end however. North African soil will reveal their capacity to espouse an unexpected cause, and to become stronger whatever the ordeal and the foes. This wonderful Serie was sold at 50 000 copies in France and is the mark of one of the greatest comics scriptwriter, Fabien Nury.
name: Insha'Halla

description: With death on the line, Dan makes a desperate play to save his PR team... but at what cost to his love life? Goodbyes are said, and the beast with two backs is made, as Public Relations brings its first story arc to a close with blood on its sword and a churro in its mouth.

First Issue Special ONLY $1.99

Have you ever felt your life is meaningless, that you are wasting your potential in a dead end job, that you were meant for something greater? Meet Raman. He's just an average 22-year-old with no idea of what the future holds for him, until one day, he decides to try and be a hero. When a young girl is threatened, Raman's uncharacteristic act of heroism leaves him on the brink of death, with three bullets in his chest. He learns that death is just the beginning. Resurrected with the power to access the abilities of his past lives: The Cursed Centurian, The Crimson Templar, The Monk, The Witch, The Magus, the Caveman and more, Raman takes on a new role as the Reincarnation Man!

Hell hath no fury like a mother scorned. CJ's relentless pursuit of her kidnapped daughter Sunflower continues, knowing full well that all roads lead to the nightmare they call Rush Bridge. We know CJ is willing to sacrifice her body to the cause, but is she willing to sacrifice her mind as well? The answer to that question will lead to a truly shocking encounter in the fourth issue of Mark Mallouk's spellbinding thriller, SUNFLOWER.

Hero Irvi and his friend Maluuk the Dwarf plan to defeat Cobra Dictator and free the people. As comedians, they invite Cobra to play in a show glorifying his reign. They expect to stab him to death when he will be alone in the middle of the stage. However, the plan turns differently, because of the presence of Sian, love-interest of Irvi, which changes everything for the Hero. The Love stronger than the Fear, the Dictator's Power and the Revolution? Artist Enrique Fernández paints a colorful and still funny and magical universe, glamourous characters and let the emotions blast the Heart.
name: Revolution

description:
Confined to their cubicles in a company run by idiot bosses, Dilbert and his white-collar colleagues make the dronelike world of Kafka seem congenial. Parasitic consultants, weaselly stockbrokers, masochistic coworkers and the ever-present, evil-plotting pointy-haired boss? Welcome to the seventh circle of hell, er, the 22nd collection of Scott Adams' stupendously popular comic strip, Dilbert!

Words You Don't Want to Hear During Your Annual Performance Review updates loyal readers on the mind-numbing careers of Dilbert, Wally, Alice, the PHB himself, and an ever-expanding cast of walk-on "guest stars." In this installment, a cash-sucking "consultick" burrows under the boss's skin, a not-so-grim reaper pops anti-depressants, and a lab accident turns Dilbert into a sheep-a transformation which goes barely noticed by his beleaguered coworkers. All the while, Adams takes his patented over-the-top but right-on-the-money jabs at the inanity of the corporate world.

Dilbert's fans are legion and loyal. They have purchased seven million cartoon collection books and counting. The Dilbert comic strip appears in 2,000 newspapers and in 65 countries in 19 languages.
name: Words You Don't Want to Hear During Your Annual Performance Review

description:
Dilbert is easily one of the most clever and consistently funny comics in current circulation. Like all great comic strips, it provides a much-needed daily dose of comedy and, most importantly, keeps its finger firmly planted on the pulse of truth while doing so. Some might think that the corporate scandals of 2002 could make it difficult to find anything funny about today's business world. But When Body Language Goes Bad proves it will take more than that to slow down the inventive wit of Scott Adams, who clearly is never at a loss for finding hysterical things to mock in corporate life.

This marks the 21st collection of Adams' wildly popular comic strip, Dilbert, which is featured in more than 2,000 newspapers worldwide. This book updates loyal readers on the so-called careers of Dilbert, Alice, Wally, Asok the intern, and other regulars as they wallow through pointless projects, mismanaged company takeovers, futile team-building exercises, and other inane company initiatives like the "name the rest room" contest.

In addition to the strips' familiar characters, this collection showcases Adams' masterful ability to create hilarious "guest stars." There's the network design engineer known as Psycho Hillbilly, who was going for the gentle biker look until he decided it was overdone. Then, there's M. T. Suit, who is merely an empty suit walking the office halls spewing corporatese, such as "promising to enhance core competencies by leveraging platforms."

Adams says that about 80 percent of his initial ideas come from his 150 million-plus readers. Those worldwide readers are sure to celebrate the humor found in When Body Language Goes Bad, his latest satirical look at the modern workplace.
name: When Body Language Goes Bad
